      "solution": "n = gets.to_i\ndata = gets.chomp.split.map(&:to_i)\nhighest = data.max\n\nhighest.downto(1) do |i|\n  line = []\n  data.each do |v|\n    if v == i\n      line << \"***\"\n    elsif v > i\n      line << \"* *\"\n    else\n      line << \"   \"\n    end\n  end\n  puts line.join(' ')\nend",
      "statement": "Printing horizontal bar graphs is way too easy, so let's make it a bit more challenging!\nGiven a data set composed of [[N]] integer values, your task is to print a vertical bar graph from it.\nFor each value [[V]] of the data set, you must print a bar that is [[V]] lines tall and 3 columns wide. Each line of the bar consists of the characters \"* *\", except for the top one, that must be \"***\". If [[V]] is zero, simply leave the bar's area empty (with white spaces).\nThe bars should be printed in the same order as the given data and separated by spaces.",
