    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Printing horizontal bar graphs is way too easy, so let's make it a bit more challenging!<br>Given a data set composed of <var>N</var> integer values, your task is to print a vertical bar graph from it.<br>For each value <var>V</var> of the data set, you must print a bar that is <var>V</var> lines tall and 3 columns wide. Each line of the bar consists of the characters &quot;* *&quot;, except for the top one, that must be &quot;***&quot;. If <var>V</var> is zero, simply leave the bar's area empty (with white spaces).<br>The bars should be printed in the same order as the given data and separated by spaces.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer <var>N</var> for the data set size<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> <var>N</var> different space separated integer values <var>V</var></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><var>N</var> space separated bars, following the description above.<br>The empty area of the graph must be filled with white spaces (for example, if the first bar is the highest one, the lines of the graph containing only this bar must be filled with trailing white spaces).</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 10<br>0 &le; <var>V</var> &le; 10</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">6\n1 5 6 5 0 4</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">        ***            \n    *** * * ***        \n    * * * * * *     ***\n    * * * * * *     * *\n    * * * * * *     * *\n*** * * * * * *     * *</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
